<HEADLINE>
<P>
FAMILY FRIEND SOUGHT IN TEEN BEATING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"A friend of the family" is being sought for questioning in the brutal beating 
of a 13-year-old girl in Hillcrest last week, authorities said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
The victim, Marcie Bradburn, was discovered about 10:30 a.m. Friday, 
unconscious and lying near the site of the abandoned Sears store at Cleveland 
and University avenues, police spokesman Bill Robinson said. 
</P>
<P>
She apparently had been beaten with a baseball bat or other heavy instrument 
and then choked. The girl lived with her mother in an apartment in the 1400 
block of Morrow Way, less than two blocks away. 
</P>
<P>
A 27-year-old man whom the family had befriended was believed to be involved in 
the beating, Robinson said, but the spokesman stopped short of calling him a 
suspect. Police did not release the man's name or his description, but said 
they believe he is still in the San Diego area. 
</P>
<P>
Bradburn is hospitalized in critical condition with extremely serious head 
injuries, according to police. Her location is being withheld because the 
assailant remains at large. 
</P>
