<TEXT>
<P>
Cal State Fullerton will try to improve its record to better than .500 tonight 
when the Titans play Fresno State in a Big West Conference game in Selland 
Arena. 
</P>
<P>
Since breaking a 7-game losing streak more than a week ago, Fullerton (8-8 
overall, 3-4 in Big West Conference play) has 3 straight victories. 
</P>
<P>
Fresno State (9-8, 4-4) broke a 3-game losing streak Thursday with a 69-52 
victory over the University of the Pacific. 
</P>
<P>
Fullerton beat Pacific, 79-75, in overtime Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
Jervis Cole, a 6-foot 6-inch senior forward, is averaging 18 points a game for 
the Bulldogs, and freshman guard Wilbert Hooker is averaging 12. 
</P>
<P>
Fullerton forward Cedric Ceballos is averaging 21 points and 9 rebounds a game, 
and guard Mark Hill is averaging 16 points. ROBYN NORWOOD 
