<P>
HECTOR LOPEZ, RUBEN CASTILLO IN SEPARATE BOUTS TONIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By EARL GUSTKEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hector Lopez, Derrick Kelly and Ruben Castillo headline tonight's boxing show 
at the Forum. 
</P>
<P>
Lopez (17-1), the No. 1-ranked (World Boxing Council) featherweight in the 
world from Glendale, meets Rogelio Lopez (16-6) from Dallas. 
</P>
<P>
Lopez, who won the Forum's featherweight tournament title last year, hasn't 
fought since last spring, after being arrested and jailed on a kidnap charge 
involving his girlfriend. 
</P>
<P>
Kelly (21-1-2), from Los Angeles, boxes Luis Santana (38-7) of Las Vegas, who 
will defend his North American Boxing Federation welterweight championship for 
the fourth time. The two met 14 months ago at the Forum, Kelly winning a 
10-round decision. 
</P>
<P>
Castillo, normally behind the microphone with Chick Hearn at Forum boxing shows 
as a Prime Ticket commentator, is launching a comeback at age 31. In a 10-round 
lightweight bout, he meets Santos Moreno (45-15) of Juarez, Mexico. 
</P>
<P>
Castillo was 66-6 when he retired in 1985. He fought four times in world title 
bouts, but never won. EARL GUSTKEY 
</P>
