<TEXT>
<P>
Uwe Jens Mey of East Germany won both the 500- and the 1,000-meter World Cup 
speed skating races at Miola di Pine, Italy, and strengthened his lead in the 
overall Cup standings. 
</P>
<P>
Mey, who leads the standings with 192 points, won the 500-meter race with a 
rink-record time of 36.99 seconds. Dan Jansen of the United States, who won at 
the same distance Saturday, finished second with a time of 37.71. 
</P>
<P>
Mey, who won in the 1,000 Saturday, also won the event Sunday with a time of 1 
minute 15.63 seconds, outdistancing Nick Thometz of the United States, who was 
second at 1:16.16. American Eric Flaim was third at 1:16.17 and Jansen fourth 
at 1:16.22. 
