<P>
Mike Holland won the U.S. national ski jumping championship, and his brother, 
Joe, won the Nordic combined national title at Lake Placid, N.Y. 
</P>
<P>
Mike Holland, 27, took the 70-meter jumping title 1 day after winning the 
90-meters. He had jumps of 86.5 and 84 meters for 219.2 points. Tad Langlois of 
Newport, N.H., was runner-up both days. 
</P>
<P>
