<TEXT>
<P>
CBS' "60 Minutes" has won the prestigious Alfred I. duPont-Columbia University 
Gold Baton Award for two decades of reporting that "changed the nature of 
television news." Network winners of Silver Batons included CBS News for 
coverage of the Persian Gulf by Allen Pizzey, NBC News for "A Conversation With 
Mikhail Gorbachev" and ABC News for "Night-line: In the Holy Land." Public 
Affairs Television and Alvin H. Perlmutter Inc. received an award for "Joseph 
Campbell and the Power of Myth, With Bill Moyers." Nina Totenberg and National 
Public Radio were honored for coverage of the Supreme Court nominations. ALEENE 
MacMINN 
